  {
    "hotel_id": "100103",
    "hotel_url": "https://www.agoda.com/grand-boracay-resort/hotel/boracay-island-ph.html",
    "name": "Grand Boracay Resort",
    "detail": "literally right in the middle of boracay island at station 2. this large, chinese owned and operated resort has one entrance on the main road with easy access to laundries, a department store, supermarket, korean restaurant and fish and chips restaurant. the second entrance is right on d'mall with dozens of boutiques, restaurants, souvenir shops, and a kodak photofinishing shop. breakfast was bountiful and healthy. two apple computers available for guest use for free. beach towels available for pool or beach use. hotel rooms are spacious, have a minibar, aircon. the hotel is not handicapped accessible, with cobblestone grounds, no elevators, and 3 storey buildings. watchout for being charged for the temporary henna tatoo marks on any bedding, towels, or pillow cases. i was charged for complete new set of bedding and towels because of the stains from the popular tatoos that exceeded the cost of the hotel room. no warning signs or statement from the staff, so this is landmine that might spoil your stay. southwest arranged transportation from kalibo airport to boracay hotel and return for a reasonable price and eliminated waiting in line and having to deal with four to six different services. ",
